704237f-a.title: Brooklyn: Flatbush Avenue - Chester Court
704237f-a.text:
610 Flatbush Ave., west side, just north of Chester Court; owned by Reuben Freeman in 1911. It was originally the Jeremiah Vanderbilt House which now (1936) is no longer standing.
1910.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, another view. In 1920 it was an antomobile supply station until torn down, about 1923. The old Vanderbilt House burnt during the Revolutionary War stood just north of this house.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
